721721f-a.text:
Morningside Drive, west side, from 117th to 119th Streets. It was originally planned to erect the new Rockefeller Baptist Church (Dr. Fosdick's church) on this site; but the plans were changed, and the church went to Riverside Drive, becoming the
Riverside Church.
June, 1925.

721711f-a.text:
Morningside Ave., east side, north from West 117th (right) to 121st Street, as viewed northeastward across Morningside Park, from
Morningside Drive.
July 1928.
George L. Balgue.
